@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About FitTrack";
}

<div class="card shadow-sm border-0 p-4">
    <h1 class="mb-3">About FitTrack</h1>

    <p>
        FitTrack is a fitness-based web application created as part of a final project using ASP.NET Core MVC.
        The purpose of this project is to provide a simple way to store and view exercises and workouts.
    </p>

    <p>
        Users can add exercises with information such as category, duration, and difficulty, and create workouts by date.
        Workouts can also display related exercises based on their category.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-4">Key Features</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Navigation menu across multiple pages</li>
        <li>Separate controllers and views using MVC</li>
        <li>Database connection using Entity Framework Core</li>
        <li>Forms with validation</li>
        <li>Exercise and workout tracking</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="mt-4">Technologies Used</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>ASP.NET Core MVC</li>
        <li>C#</li>
        <li>Entity Framework Core</li>
        <li>SQL Server LocalDB</li>
        <li>Bootstrap</li>
        <li>Git and GitHub</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="mt-4">Why Fitness?</h3>
    <p>
        Fitness was chosen because it is a practical and relatable hobby that works well with a database-driven application.
        It also allows data to be organized in a way that makes sense for real-world use.
    </p>
</div>